==English==

===Etymology===
Figurative sense US from 1846.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=[[scare]] [[up]]|scares up|scaring up|scared up}}

# To frighten (an animal, especially a game animal) into appearing from cover.
#* '''1881''', {{w|Henry David Thoreau}}, ''Early Spring in Massachusetts'':
#*: Soon after, we '''scare up''' a flock of black ducks.
#* '''1913''', [[w:Jack London|Jack London]], ''The Cruise of the "Snark"'', 2008, [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=Qg21_f_tKSkC&pg=PT99&dq=%22scaring+up%22%7C%22scared+up%22%7C%22scares+up%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MrGkUe7TNc2QkQWRuYDwAg&redir_esc=y unnumbered page],
#*: They ranged along abreast of the Snark on either side, pouncing upon the flying-fish her forefoot '''scared up'''.
#* '''2004''', William Barksdale Maynard, ''Walden Pond'', [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=I9z2SqSmIy4C&pg=PA105&dq=%22scaring+up%22%7C%22scared+up%22%7C%22scares+up%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MrGkUe7TNc2QkQWRuYDwAg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22scaring%20up%22%7C%22scared%20up%22%7C%22scares%20up%22&f=false page 105],
#*: In September, Henry walked Emerson's frequent route, Hosmer's-Goose Pond-Walden, and viewed the pond from the hill on the north side with the sawed pine stump atop, '''scaring up''' black ducks.
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} To [[find]] or [[procure]], especially something not easily found or procured.
#* '''1881''', William Dean Howells, ''A Modern Instance'', page 185:
#*: “By the way,” said his friend, “let’s go over into Leopoldstadt, and see if we can’t '''scare up''' a sleigh for a little turn in the suburbs.”
#* '''1990''', [[w:Miller's Crossing|Miller's Crossing]], 01:25:07
#*: "'''Scare''' me '''up''' some [[gargle]], will you?"
#* '''2003''', Stephanie Stein Crease, ''Gil Evans: Out of the Cool: His Life and Music'', [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=b-5GoNQzsbQC&pg=PA6&dq=%22scaring+up%22%7C%22scared+up%22%7C%22scares+up%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MrGkUe7TNc2QkQWRuYDwAg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22scaring%20up%22%7C%22scared%20up%22%7C%22scares%20up%22&f=false page 6],
#*: Gil also '''scared up''' other part-time jobs while in high school—delivering gas canisters and playing solo piano at tea time at the elegant Hotel Stockton.
#* '''2004''', Michael Streissguth, ''Voices of the Country: Interviews With Classic Country Performers'', [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=1R1TiXZH4moC&pg=PA80&dq=%22scaring+up%22%7C%22scared+up%22%7C%22scares+up%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MrGkUe7TNc2QkQWRuYDwAg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22scaring%20up%22%7C%22scared%20up%22%7C%22scares%20up%22&f=false page 80],
#*: Now, whenever he's in Nashville '''scaring up''' clients and I'm there '''scaring up''' stories, we hit the hillbilly circuit.
#* '''2005''', Stephen J. Cannell, ''Cold Hit'', page 367:
#*: “With the current budget crunch and the Fingertip case inactive, I couldn’t '''scare up''' much enthusiasm.”

